\pard\sl240\slmult1\qj\f0\fs20\lang9 What Are Networking Protocols?\par
\par
A network protocol is a set of rules and standards that define how data is transmitted, formatted, and received between devices.\par
\par
Think of it like language rules in communication.\par
\par
Example:\par
\par
When you send a message online, protocols decide:\par
\par
how the message is packaged\par
\par
where it is sent\par
\par
how it is verified\par
\par
how it is received\par
\par
Without protocols, computers cannot understand each other.\par
\par
2. Why Networking Protocols Are Important in Cybersecurity\par
\par
Protocols are critical because they affect:\par
\par
1\u-497?\f1\u8419?\f0  Data Transmission Security\par
\par
They control how data moves across networks.\par
\par
Example:\par
\par
HTTP \f2\u8594?\f3  \f0 not secure\par
\par
HTTPS \f2\u8594?\f3  \f0 encrypted and secure\par
\par
2\u-497?\f1\u8419?\f0  Authentication\par
\par
Protocols can verify who is allowed to access a network.\par
\par
Example:\par
\par
Kerberos\par
\par
RADIUS\par
\par
3\u-497?\f1\u8419?\f0  Encryption\par
\par
Some protocols encrypt data to protect confidentiality.\par
\par
Example:\par
\par
SSL/TLS\par
\par
IPsec\par
\par
4\u-497?\f1\u8419?\f0  Network Monitoring\par
\par
Security teams analyze protocol traffic to detect attacks like:\par
\par
Malware communication\par
\par
Data exfiltration\par
\par
Command & Control traffic\par
\par
Tools used:\par
\par
Wireshark\par
\par
Snort\par
\par
Zeek\par
\par
3. Protocols and the OSI Model\par
\par
Networking protocols operate in layers defined by the OSI model.\par
\par
There are 7 layers.\par
\par
Layer\tab Function\tab Example Protocols\par
Application\tab User interaction\tab HTTP, FTP\par
Presentation\tab Encryption & formatting\tab SSL/TLS\par
Session\tab Session management\tab NetBIOS\par
Transport\tab Data delivery\tab TCP, UDP\par
Network\tab Routing\tab IP, ICMP\par
Data Link\tab MAC communication\tab ARP\par
Physical\tab Hardware transmission\tab Ethernet\par
\par
Cybersecurity professionals must know which protocol works at which layer.\par
\par
