6. Common Protocol Attacks\par
Man-in-the-Middle Attack\par
\par
Attacker intercepts communication between two systems.\par
\par
Protocols targeted:\par
\par
ARP\par
\par
HTTP\par
\par
DNS\par
\par
DNS Spoofing\par
\par
Fake DNS responses redirect users to malicious websites.\par
\par
SYN Flood Attack\par
\par
Overloads a server by sending many TCP connection requests.\par
\par
Packet Sniffing\par
\par
Attackers capture network packets to steal:\par
\par
passwords\par
\par
cookies\par
\par
credentials\par
\par
Tools:\par
\par
Wireshark\par
\par
Tcpdump\par
\par
